## Subnetting

Now we will tackle the allegedly scary monster that is subnetting. For this one overarching topic I am going to divide it into four sequential sections:

- Classful
- Classless
- Magic Number
- Seven Second

All four of these have their own respective uses for someone like you or me who is about to start losing their sanity to this. The key difference is at least we know how to lose our said sanity. But why would we even need to do this? Why would anyone in their right mind, not only read the primer and internalize the binary math concept but also question reality as they deal with what class of IP address, how to subnet and etc?

The real answer is because subnetting fulfills a few key purposes. The concept of subnetting itself is to make sure that a network, which means our building where our rooms are held, is divided and managed into tiny subnetworks (subnets) or rooms to improve performance, security and how efficient we dish out IP addresses or the ID cards for our objects.

